cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation classification. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization of the instance selection and relation classification processes, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques could also suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
